From: Your Name <your.email@example.com>
Subject: [PATCH] recipes-bsp/secure-boot: Make supported machines list configurable

The current implementation hardcodes the list of supported machines in
the python __anonymous() function. This makes it difficult for BSP layers
to add support for custom boards without modifying meta-qoriq-bsp directly.

This patch introduces QORIQ_SECUREBOOT_SUPPORTED_MACHINES variable that
can be extended via .bbappend files.

Benefits:
- BSP layers can add their machines without modifying meta-qoriq-bsp
- Follows Yocto best practices for layer customization
- Backward compatible - default behavior unchanged

Signed-off-by: Your Name <your.email@example.com>
---
 .../recipes-bsp/secure-boot/secure-boot-qoriq.bb | 5 ++++-
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/meta-qoriq-bsp/recipes-bsp/secure-boot/secure-boot-qoriq.bb b/meta-qoriq-bsp/recipes-bsp/secure-boot/secure-boot-qoriq.bb
index ce435b3..a1b2c45 100644
--- a/meta-qoriq-bsp/recipes-bsp/secure-boot/secure-boot-qoriq.bb
+++ b/meta-qoriq-bsp/recipes-bsp/secure-boot/secure-boot-qoriq.bb
@@ -3,9 +3,12 @@ SECTION = "bootloaders"
 LICENSE = "GPL-2.0-only"
 LIC_FILES_CHKSUM = "file://${COMMON_LICENSE_DIR}/GPL-2.0-only;md5=801f80980d171dd6425610833a22dbe6"
 
+# Configurable list of supported machines
+QORIQ_SECUREBOOT_SUPPORTED_MACHINES ??= "ls1012afrwy ls1012ardb ls1021atwr ls1028ardb ls1043ardb ls1046afrwy ls1046ardb ls1088ardb ls1088ardb-pb ls2088ardb lx2160ardb-rev2 lx2162aqds"
+
 python __anonymous () {
-    board="ls1012afrwy ls1012ardb ls1021atwr ls1028ardb ls1043ardb ls1046afrwy ls1046ardb ls1088ardb ls1088ardb-pb ls2088ardb lx2160ardb-rev2 lx2162aqds"
+    board = d.getVar("QORIQ_SECUREBOOT_SUPPORTED_MACHINES")
     m = d.getVar("MACHINE")
-    if m not in board:
+    if m not in board.split():
         raise bb.parse.SkipRecipe("This platform not exit secure-boot manifest")
 }
-- 
